reviews.text:
The customer service was exceptional. The food was a bonus on top. My son raved about the burger and the quality was superb. My mother was beyond impressed with the customer service and her wings. I have to say the smash burger was definitely noteworthy of ordering again. I/we recommend anyone who is looking to enjoy an exquisite burger, along with a commendable menu selection, and excellent customer service.
Check it out, I don‚Äôt think you will regret it!

I had heard some good things about Secret Burger Kitchen so I set out to see for myself. The location is within the Holiday Inn Hotel off of 84th on Hosmer. Not the most upscale of areas so it really surprised me how much this dining experience cost me.
The staff was great. A young lady showed me the kiosk that you can order and pay through. The order (a signature 1/3 lb cheese burger with bacon and a chop Philly cheese. Both came with fries) came quickly and was nicely packaged for takeout. It was still plenty hot eating it at home.
The quality and taste was a solid 8 out of 10 so I was happy that what I had heard about the place was accurate.
Unfortunately I won't be going back. The meal we had (which I will simply cook at home next time) rang up after a 15% tip to nearly $45. Come on, guys. I mean, $25 would have kept me coming back from time to time to try other menu items. But nope.
The place was clean and the food is good. Price? smh

Whoa baby!!! These smash burgers are legit!!! Finally, a seasoned patty! Tasty. Crispy. Delicious.

It's located in the bottom of a hotel, which is genius! Easy to order from the kiosk. Get your receipt and find a seat.

It was ready pretty quick and a feast for the eyes. That crispy edge beef lace peeked beyond the bun and straight to yum town!

We were in the area so we decided to check this place out. I went with the double smash and fries.
The burger was good. Perfectly cooked burger, the fries were crispy and fresh. The fry sauce was good it had a little bit of spice which I did like. The service was good the staff were nice  and welcoming. There was plenty of parking and the inside was nice and clean and they also have a few tables outside. Over all the food was good but I think it was pricey. $17 for double burger and fries without a dink.

I had a really great time at the is place. This was the Tacoma location. The service was awesome!! And they had outside sheeting which was nice. The time me and my boyfriend went it wasn‚Äôt too busy which was good. We got two different milkshakes and they were so yummy and the food was amazing I loved how crispy the fries were too!! One of the owners even came out and spoke with us for a bit and I thought that was so genuine and thoughtful I‚Äôd definitely recommend!:)

detailedReviews.author: Anthony Vanderlinde
detailedReviews.text: First of all, no one eats as many burgers as I do! I absolutely love hamburgers! I‚Äôve ate burgers all over the country and outside the US. This double smash burger with cheese with the SBK sauce and jalape√±os/Serrano peppers was the best burger I‚Äôve had hands down! I did go in on a Friday night at about 10:30pm and was the only customers eating at this time. The burger was perfect! The beef pattie‚Äôs were so hot temp wise it almost burned my tongue! The beef was cooked perfect and very flavorful. You could tell it was top quality beef. I see some reviews saying they waited forever for a cold burned burger, well I suggest go in on off times when it‚Äôs slow and you won‚Äôt be disappointed! Can‚Äôt wait to get back for another round! It‚Äôs definitely made my list as the number one best burger in Tacoma with Beach Tavern coming in second now, which used to be the best burger in Tacoma. Sorry Beach, this place took your top spot on my list. Again I think I eat more burgers then anyone lol

If I happen to be in the area I would give it another shot.

detailedReviews.author: Yvonne Holmes
detailedReviews.text:
After all the rave reviews, we were looking forward to trying what many people said was "the best hamburger ever".
The place  was crowded when we got there and there were many "to go" orders. We were fine with a wait as we expected the burgers to be something worth waiting for. The servers were pleasant enough (although they looked a little understaffed). After a good 45 minute wait, our burgers came out and looked absolutely nothing like the pictures. Mine was burned to a crisp. Totally dry and overcooked. The was minimal sauce and a very small segment of a piece of lettuce. Again, nothing like the pictures. All I could taste was the totally charred, dry meat and salt. Such a disappointment  after all this hype and a very expensive burger that was totally overpriced for what was presented. I'm guessing a person's impression would vary based on who is in the kitchen cooking the food. We obviously had someone working who was more concerned in just getting food out, regardless if it caught on fire and burned, than caring about the quality. We do not plan to return.

detailedReviews.author: dawg 7579
detailedReviews.text:
I cannot believe all the favorable reviews for this place.  Several diners saying it was the best burger they ever had. I would say it was one of the worst I've ever had.  Over cooked, dry. I gave the food rating a 2 because the fries were pretty good.  We waited 45 minutes for a hamburger!
Service was okay though sparse, meaning they seemed very inexperienced and understaffed.  I asked for water 3 times and never got it until I was leaving and was handed a bottle of water.
Ambience nonexistent.  It is in a Holiday Inn in a very sketchy part of Tacoma and the to go clientele which made up the majority of the customers reflected this.  I would never suggest anyone to go there unless they were staying at the hotel and had no other choice.

probably the worst service lol i ordered for pick up in advance (as it‚Äôs saturday‚Äî wait times can be expected). i came in early and asked if my food was ready, which was a no (duhh, right?), and sat down to wait again. ~10 minutes later, i get a text that my food was ready so i go up and ask again. she says no and now i‚Äôm confused, but sit down and wait anyways. as i‚Äôm waiting, i hear people asking if their food was ready and they said no, and say that it‚Äôs ___(insert my name)‚Äôs order. i shot up and told them that i‚Äôve been waiting awhile and asked if my food was ready (it‚Äôs been 45 minutes at this point). they said they didn‚Äôt know my name and they wouldn‚Äôt have known. i replied saying i did tell them TWICE and have just been sitting here waiting. they called out everybody‚Äôs orders by their names/numbers except for me. i‚Äôm so pissed. my food‚Äôs cold and isn‚Äôt even good. i placed my order at 5:00pm and didn‚Äôt leave until 6pm. i was super excited to try this place, but was left very very disappointed. the bag was behind them for awhile, while other names were called right out the kitchen. i was sitting there with a ready text for 45 mins! not once did i hear my name, AND i went up and asked multiple times. i understand the wait as it‚Äôs a saturday, but don‚Äôt say it‚Äôs ready when it‚Äôs not‚Ä¶. or have attentive service lol.

side note, the shake was also lacking flavor and literally just white mush with stale cereal on top. the food‚Äôs cold and dry now. i‚Äôm so disappointed as a service worker myself.
